\begin_layout Abstract

\lang english
Sustainability assessment processes in agriculture are characterized by
 complexity, interdisciplinarity and continuous changes.
 Sustainability experts from Embrapa Environment defined the SustenAgro
 Method for sustainability assessment of sugarcane production systems in
 the central-south region of Brazil.
 In this work, a methodology based on ontologies (using the Web Ontology
 Language - OWL) and Domain Specific Languages (DSLs) is presented.
 It was used successfully in the implementation of the Decision Support
 System (DSS) SustenAgro.
 This system was evaluated by sustainability experts from Embrapa.
 The results showed that its user interface works well and that its sustainabili
ty reports are correct (according to the SustenAgro Method).
\end_layout

